<span id="freeTextContainer12998764248577386062">Usually enjoy retellings of Beauty and the Beast, but I loathed this one. There&apos;s not much to like in Ethan and I could not get past the annoying, phonetically written accent. Maddy comes across as self-centred and wanton, with no sense of honour. The author&apos;s modern style of dialogue made it hard to imagine that the story was taking place in the late 19th century.</span>
